            <gmd:abstract>
                <gco:CharacterString>The Swift Current Creek Watershed Stewards in collaboration with the Carrot River Watershed Association, South Saskatchewan River Watershed Stewards, and North Saskatchewan River Basin aim to sample phosphorus levels in tributaries that contribute to the Lake Winnipeg Basin. Samples were taken with standard “grab” protocol at pre-determined sites within each watershed with the help of volunteers as citizen scientists. All samples were sent for laboratory analysis. High phosphorus levels in the Lake Winnipeg basin have been documented and  sources explored as to where the phosphorus loading is coming from. The Swift Current Creek, located in South Saskatchewan, is the largest tributary to the South Saskatchewan River, which feeds into the Lake Winnipeg basin.</gco:CharacterString>

name: 10-25976-0k58-0q19
notes: The Swift Current Creek Watershed Stewards in collaboration with the Carrot River Watershed Association, South Saskatchewan River Watershed Stewards, and North Saskatchewan River Basin aim to sample phosphorus levels in tributaries that contribute to the Lake Winnipeg Basin. Samples were taken with standard “grab” protocol at pre-determined sites within each watershed with the help of volunteers as citizen scientists. All samples were sent for laboratory analysis. High phosphorus levels in the Lake Winnipeg basin have been documented and  sources explored as to where the phosphorus loading is coming from. The Swift Current Creek, located in South Saskatchewan, is the largest tributary to the South Saskatchewan River, which feeds into the Lake Winnipeg basin.

notes_translated.en: The Swift Current Creek Watershed Stewards in collaboration with the Carrot River Watershed Association, South Saskatchewan River Watershed Stewards, and North Saskatchewan River Basin aim to sample phosphorus levels in tributaries that contribute to the Lake Winnipeg Basin. Samples were taken with standard “grab” protocol at pre-determined sites within each watershed with the help of volunteers as citizen scientists. All samples were sent for laboratory analysis. High phosphorus levels in the Lake Winnipeg basin have been documented and  sources explored as to where the phosphorus loading is coming from. The Swift Current Creek, located in South Saskatchewan, is the largest tributary to the South Saskatchewan River, which feeds into the Lake Winnipeg basin.
notes_translated.fr: Les responsables du bassin versant de Swift Current Creek, en collaboration avec la Carrot River Watershed Association, les South Saskatchewan River Watershed Stewards et le North Saskatchewan River Basin, visent à échantillonner les niveaux de phosphore dans les affluents qui contribuent au bassin du lac Winnipeg. Des échantillons ont été prélevés selon un protocole standard de prélèvement sur des sites prédéterminés de chaque bassin versant avec l'aide de bénévoles en tant que scientifiques citoyens. Tous les échantillons ont été envoyés pour analyse en laboratoire. Des niveaux élevés de phosphore dans le bassin du lac Winnipeg ont été documentés et des sources ont été explorées pour déterminer d'où provient la charge de phosphore. Le ruisseau Swift Current, situé dans le sud de la Saskatchewan, est le plus grand affluent de la rivière Saskatchewan Sud, qui se jette dans le bassin du lac Winnipeg.
